{
  "text": "Item 21. Preschool teachers report that they do not consider more activities with water to be necessary in their classroom. However, Pedersen & McCurdy [CITATION_1] support that \"Nature is considered to be important for young children in terms of experiences and learning outcomes compared with other curricular areas\".",
